<hr class="post-separator" aria-hidden="true" />
<article id="post-5859" class="post-5859 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-exhibits category-sc">
			<header class="entry-header">
			<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/2017/04/new-exhibition-canada-150-picturing-the-canadian-landscape/">New Exhibition: Canada 150, Picturing the Canadian Landscape</a></h1>
		</header><!-- .entry-header -->
	
	<div class="entry-content">

				<div class="entry-meta">
			<span class="sep">Posted on </span><a href="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/2017/04/new-exhibition-canada-150-picturing-the-canadian-landscape/" title="4:23 pm" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2017-04-19T16:23:56-04:00" pubdate>April 19, 2017</time></a><span class="by-author"> <span class="sep"> by </span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/author/askyrme/" title="View all posts by Alison" rel="author">Alison</a></span></span>		</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
		
		
<div>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="alignleft is-resized"><a href="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/2017/04/new-exhibition-canada-150-picturing-the-canadian-landscape/picturingthecanadianlandscape/" rel="attachment wp-att-5860"><img data-attachment-id="5860" data-permalink="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/2017/04/new-exhibition-canada-150-picturing-the-canadian-landscape/picturingthecanadianlandscape/" data-orig-file="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/04/PicturingTheCanadianLandscape.jpg" data-orig-size="2204,3207" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;2.2&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;iPhone 5s&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1492617124&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;4.15&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;200&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.033333333333333&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="PicturingTheCanadianLandscape" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/04/PicturingTheCanadianLandscape-206x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/04/PicturingTheCanadianLandscape-412x600.jpg" loading="lazy" src="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/04/PicturingTheCanadianLandscape-412x600.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-5860" width="299" height="435" srcset="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/04/PicturingTheCanadianLandscape-412x600.jpg 412w, https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/04/PicturingTheCanadianLandscape-103x150.jpg 103w, https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/04/PicturingTheCanadianLandscape-206x300.jpg 206w, https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/04/PicturingTheCanadianLandscape-768x1118.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 299px) 100vw, 299px" /></a><figcaption>Canada 150: Picturing the Canadian Landscape.&nbsp;Ryerson Library Archives and Special Collections</figcaption></figure></div>



<p>The plains of the prairies, the forests of the interior, and the seascapes of the Atlantic and the Pacific have served as muses for Canadian artists and writers for centuries.</p>



<p>In Canada 150: Picturing the Canadian Landscape, photographs and ephemera of the <a href="https://archives.library.ryerson.ca/index.php/lorne-shields-historical-photograph-collection">Lorne Shields Historical Photograph&nbsp;Collection</a>&nbsp;at Ryerson University showcase the ways in which the natural landscape has been an essential part of the identity and history of Canada.</p>



<p>Incorporating&nbsp;extraordinary cameras from the&nbsp;<a href="https://archives.library.ryerson.ca/index.php/heritage-camera-collection">Heritage Camera Collection</a> and the <a href="https://archives.library.ryerson.ca/index.php/kodak-canada-corporate-archives-and-heritage-collection">Kodak Canada Corporate Archives and Heritage Collection</a>, and rare books from Ryerson University’s Special Collections, this exhibition reflects on the photographic, recreational, and artistic responses to Canada’s natural landscape by artists, enthusiasts and writers throughout the years.</p>



<div style="height:26px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<p>Drop by the Archives and Special Collections Department, on the &nbsp;4th floor of the Ryerson Library, to see the exhibition, curated by&nbsp;Image Arts students Bowie Fan, Gabriele Tai, Georgia Love, Justine Marasigan, and Lodoe Laura.</p>
<div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"><div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-icon-text sd-sharing"><h3 class="sd-title">Share this:</h3><div class="sd-content"><ul><li><a href="#" class="sharing-anchor sd-button share-more"><span>Share</span></a></li><li class="share-end"></li></ul><div class="sharing-hidden"><div class="inner" style="display: none;"><ul><li class="share-tumblr"><a rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" data-shared="" class="share-tumblr sd-button share-icon" href="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/2017/04/new-exhibition-canada-150-picturing-the-canadian-landscape/?share=tumblr" target="_blank" title="Click to share on Tumblr"><span>Tumblr</span></a></li><li class="share-reddit"><a rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" data-shared="" class="share-reddit sd-button share-icon" href="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/2017/04/new-exhibition-canada-150-picturing-the-canadian-landscape/?share=reddit" target="_blank" title="Click to share on Reddit"><span>Reddit</span></a></li><li class="share-end"></li><li class="share-linkedin"><a rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" data-shared="sharing-linkedin-5859" class="share-linkedin sd-button share-icon" href="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/2017/04/new-exhibition-canada-150-picturing-the-canadian-landscape/?share=linkedin" target="_blank" title="Click to share on LinkedIn"><span>LinkedIn</span></a></li><li class="share-email"><a rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" data-shared="" class="share-email sd-button share-icon" href="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/2017/04/new-exhibition-canada-150-picturing-the-canadian-landscape/?share=email" target="_blank" title="Click to email this to a friend"><span>Email</span></a></li><li class="share-end"></li><li class="share-end"></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div>		
		
