<article id="post-5823" class="post-5823 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-sc">
			<header class="entry-header">
			<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/2017/02/the-2017-first-edition-book-award-winners/">The 2017 First Edition Book Award Winners</a></h1>
		</header><!-- .entry-header -->
	
	<div class="entry-content">

				<div class="entry-meta">
			<span class="sep">Posted on </span><a href="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/2017/02/the-2017-first-edition-book-award-winners/" title="10:14 am" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2017-02-13T10:14:26-05:00" pubdate>February 13, 2017</time></a><span class="by-author"> <span class="sep"> by </span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/author/askyrme/" title="View all posts by Alison" rel="author">Alison</a></span></span>		</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
		
		
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter"><a href="http://library.ryerson.ca/asc/2017/02/the-2017-first-edition-book-award-winners/compilation-2/" rel="attachment wp-att-5832"><img data-attachment-id="5832" data-permalink="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/2017/02/the-2017-first-edition-book-award-winners/compilation-2/" data-orig-file="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/02/Compilation-2.jpg" data-orig-size="1800,3375" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;8&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;Canon EOS 5D Mark II&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1486465716&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;35&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;100&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.008&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Compilation 2" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/02/Compilation-2-160x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/02/Compilation-2-320x600.jpg" loading="lazy" width="320" height="600" src="http://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/02/Compilation-2-320x600.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-5832" srcset="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/02/Compilation-2-320x600.jpg 320w, https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/02/Compilation-2-80x150.jpg 80w, https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/02/Compilation-2-160x300.jpg 160w, https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/02/Compilation-2-768x1440.jpg 768w, https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/02/Compilation-2.jpg 1800w" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px" /></a><figcaption>Winners of the 2017 First Edition Book Award</figcaption></figure></div>



<h2>Award Recipients</h2>



<p class="has-text-align-left">Adrian Walton-Cordeiro &#8211; <em>Contesse De Bertren</em><br>Ailene Devries &#8211; <em>Two Cities and a River</em><br>Fehn Foss &#8211; <em>Remembering, Faring</em><br>Julia Garnet &#8211; <em>Elements</em><br>Feline Gerhardt &#8211; <em>About Mankind and the Attempt to Increase Significance</em><br>Warren Rynkun &#8211; <em>The Yard</em></p>



<h2>Honourable Mentions</h2>



<p>Grayson Alabiso-Cahil &#8211; <em>We’re not the first, and we won’t be the last</em><br>Rena Balmain-Matthews &#8211;<em> Poems</em><br>Jana Beaton &#8211;<em> Wallpaper Floorboards</em><br>April Beatson &#8211;<em> Skate</em><br>Rebecca Bentolila and Natasha Serio &#8211;<em> Yours and Mine</em></p>



<h2>About the Award</h2>



<p>As part of MPS507, a 3rd year Ryerson University Image Arts class in The Photographic Book, students are expected to conceive of and create their own photobook. This is, in part, related to work that has been completed in the co-requisite class, MPS506 &#8211; Photographic Production. These are both required courses for the Bachelor of Fine Arts (Image Arts) Photography Studies Option. Each year, the Library purchases the top photobooks in the class, as judged by the Special Collections Librarian, Alison Skyrme, and a special invited guest (this year Robyn York of Anchorless Press). The library pays fair market value for each book, and commits to spending a maximum of $1000 per semester. The books are judged at the First Edition Photobook Show – an exhibition of the photobooks at the end of the semester. For evaluation, particular attention is paid to design, sequencing, and integration of images and text. The library catalogues each book, including a note about the award, and houses the books in Special Collections. Occasional exhibits are created to showcase the works.</p>



<h2>History</h2>



<p>The First Edition Photobook Award was established in 2015 by Image Arts instructor Christopher Manson and the Ryerson Library to honour 3rd year photography students who have made exceptional achievements in photobook production. It provides incentive for them to achieve early recognition that will have a lasting legacy in our collection.</p>



<h2>Previous Award Recipients</h2>



<p>The following 2016 award winners were presented with a certificate during the Image Arts Awards Night, November 19th, 2016: Andrea Chartrand, Kaya Kelley, Mina Markovic, Terence Reeves, Gabriel Steele, Alia Youssef.</p>



<h2>2017 Award Winners</h2>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="alignright"><a href="http://library.ryerson.ca/asc/2017/02/the-2017-first-edition-book-award-winners/warren-rynkun-the-yard-inside-spread/" rel="attachment wp-att-5838"><img data-attachment-id="5838" data-permalink="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/2017/02/the-2017-first-edition-book-award-winners/warren-rynkun-the-yard-inside-spread/" data-orig-file="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/02/Warren-Rynkun-The-Yard-inside-spread.jpg" data-orig-size="1280,800" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;8&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;Canon EOS 5D Mark II&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1486465789&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;35&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;100&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.008&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Warren Rynkun &#8211; The Yard (inside spread)" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/02/Warren-Rynkun-The-Yard-inside-spread-300x188.jpg" data-large-file="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/02/Warren-Rynkun-The-Yard-inside-spread-600x375.jpg" loading="lazy" width="600" height="375" src="http://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/02/Warren-Rynkun-The-Yard-inside-spread-600x375.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-5838" srcset="https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/02/Warren-Rynkun-The-Yard-inside-spread-600x375.jpg 600w, https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/02/Warren-Rynkun-The-Yard-inside-spread-150x94.jpg 150w, https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/02/Warren-Rynkun-The-Yard-inside-spread-300x188.jpg 300w, https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/02/Warren-Rynkun-The-Yard-inside-spread-768x480.jpg 768w, https://library.ryerson.ca/asc/files/2017/02/Warren-Rynkun-The-Yard-inside-spread.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600p